                <h1 class="text-center">DTI Academy Competency Assessment (COMPASS) Platform</h1>
                <h2 class="text-center">PRIVACY NOTICE</h2>
                <hr>
                <p>The Department of Trade and Industry (DTI) Academy fully supports the Data Privacy Act of 2012 and shall endeavor to comply with all issuances from the National Privacy Commission (NPC).</p>
        
                <h3>Personal Information</h3>
                <p>DTI Academy collects and maintains personal information (i.e. Full Name, Age, Gender, Contact Information, Employment Details) and sensitive personal information (i.e. Civil Status, Disability Profile, Ethnicity, Religion,) in accordance with the Department Order 18-45.</p>
        
                <h3>Collection</h3>
                <p>Personal information may be collected strictly through the Competency Assessment (Compass) platform at <a href="https://dticompass.dti.gov.ph">dticompass.dti.gov.ph</a>.</p>
        
                <h3>Processing</h3>
                <p>Personal information will only be processed for the purpose of understanding your needs and to provide a better service, in accordance with the Department Order 18-45, particularly for the following reasons:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Learning and Development Needs:</strong> We use your information stored in the Compass platform to identify competency gaps, conduct training needs analysis to identify future course offerings of the DTI Academy, and to create a learning pathway for a new curriculum under Project Dalubhasa.</li>
                    <li><strong>Communication:</strong> We use your information to send you notifications and announcements regarding your learning pathways. We also use your information to be able to respond to your questions, requests, concerns, and other training-related assistance that you might need.</li>
                    <li><strong>Personnel Record:</strong> We keep your personal information to ensure that we maintain non-discriminatory and ethical human resource decisions. We also monitor equality and diversity in the group to identify current and future needs of each member of the organization.</li>
                </ol>
        
                <h3>Storage and Access</h3>
                <p>The personal information is stored with the DTI Academy under the Human Resource and Administrative Service (HRAS). Access to personal information is restricted only to concerned staff who are authorized to access such.</p>
        
                <h3>Sharing</h3>
                <p>The information we collect from you is shared with the following parties for your personal development and for the benefit of the Community of Learners in DTI Academy:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Third-Party Software:</strong> Your personal Information may be shared with the Integrated Human Resource Information System (IHRIS) of the Human Resource Management Division for internal record keeping and any other purposes related to your employment in the Department.</li>
                    <li><strong>Third-Party Contractor:</strong> The information you provide in the Compass may be accessed by the authorized personnel of our third-party contractor, Razza Consulting Group, Inc. as one of the System Administrators of the Compass Platform.</li>
                    <li><strong>Government Authorities:</strong> Any government authority asking for your personal data in writing, provided that it does not fall under the exceptions to the right of access to information of Executive Order No. 2, series of 2016 or the Freedom of Information Act (FOI) or there is a court order/subpoena addressed to the DTI Academy, to comply with the legal process.</li>
                </ol>
        
                <h3>Security Measures</h3>
                <p>The DTI Academy is committed to exercising due diligence to maintain the Privacy and Confidentiality of the Employees’ Personal Information stored in the DTI Academy Compass. We have established appropriate physical, technical, and organizational security measures in our platform to safeguard the data against accidental and unlawful loss or destruction; alteration or contamination; physical security breach; data breach; accidental exposure to unauthorized personnel; unauthorized disclosure of collected personal information; and other means of unlawful processing of information of the data in the DTI Academy Compass, thus, preserving its integrity.</p>
                <p>Any person or entity who knowingly and unlawfully violated the data confidentiality and security measures of the DTI Academy Compass; or process the personal information without the consent of the data subject or under the existing laws shall be penalized depending on the degree of violation(s) as defined in Rule XIII of Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) of Republic Act 10173 or otherwise known as the Data Privacy Act (DPA) of 2012 and other existing laws.</p>
        
                <h3>Data Subject Rights</h3>
                <p>Pursuant to the DPA, data subjects have the right to object to processes that concern their personal information. You also have the right to have access to, rectify, or request for erasure or blocking of the submitted information. You may also request to obtain a copy of their personal information and electronically move, copy, or transfer their data in a secure manner.</p>
                <p>If any of your data privacy rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with the NPC and may be indemnified for any damages sustained from such violations.</p>
        
                <h3>Retention and Disposal</h3>
                <p>The personal information you shared with us shall be retained in the DTI Academy Compass platform for as long as necessary to the fulfillment of its purpose of why it was collected; or as needed to meet other requirements in relation to your employment in the Department of Trade and Industry.</p>
                <p>After which, personal data shall be disposed or discarded in a secure manner that would prevent further processing, unauthorized access, or disclosure to any other party or the public, or prejudice the interests of the data subjects.</p>
        
                <h3>Correction of Personal Information</h3>
                <p>Should you wish to access or correct any personal information which you have provided in the past, please send an email to <a href="mailto:dtiacademy@dti.gov.ph">dtiacademy@dti.gov.ph</a>.</p>
